Adult male.description: Kentucky Warblers lack the hooded look of male Hooded Warblers and have more facial markings than female Hooded Warblers.

Female.description: Female Kentucky Warblers have more markings on the face than female Hooded Warblers.

Adult female (Northern).description: Yellow warblers have brighter yellow backs than Hooded Warblers. No white tail flashes as in Hooded Warblers.

Adult male.description: Wilson's Warblers are smaller than Hooded Warblers without a strong distinction between the face and the back like female Hooded Warblers. Lacks white tail flashes.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Wilson's Warblers are smaller than Hooded Warblers without a strong distinction between the face and the back like female Hooded Warblers. Lacks white tail flashes.

Adult male.description: Male Common Yellowthroats have a black mask and yellow throat while male Hooded Warblers have a black hood and black throat.

Female.description: Female Common Yellowthroats only have yellow on the throat and undertail coverts while female Hooded Warblers have entirely yellow bellies.
